[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Performance Benchmarks
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Metric | Expected Value | Notes |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |--------|---------------|-------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AUC-ROC (C-statistic) | 0.68-0.75 | Depends on feature richness; social determinants push toward upper range |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Calibration slope | 0.90-1.10 | After Platt scaling; check quarterly |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Brier score | 0.12-0.16 | Lower is better; baseline (prevalence) ~0.13 |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Sensitivity at top 15% | 0.35-0.45 | Captures 35-45% of actual readmissions in top risk tier |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | PPV at top 15% | 0.28-0.38 | 28-38% of flagged patients actually readmit |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Scoring latency | <500ms | End-to-end from feature assembly to score storage |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Time from discharge to score | <2 hours | Includes ADT event propagation delay |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Model retraining frequency | Monthly | Or when AUC drops below 0.65 |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Where It Struggles
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Patients with no prior history at your facility.** New patients or transfers from other systems have sparse feature vectors. The model defaults to population-level risk, which is less useful.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Social determinant-driven readmissions.** A patient readmitted because they couldn't afford their medications or had no transportation to follow-up won't be well-predicted by clinical features alone.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Planned readmissions misclassified as unplanned.** The CMS planned readmission algorithm isn't perfect. Some planned returns get labeled as failures, inflating your apparent readmission rate.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Weekend and holiday discharges.** Patients discharged when follow-up resources are unavailable have elevated risk that's driven by system factors, not patient factors. The model may not capture this well unless day-of-week features are included.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Rapidly changing care patterns.** If your hospital launches a new heart failure program that dramatically reduces CHF readmissions, the model trained on pre-program data will over-predict risk for CHF patients until retrained.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Why This Isn't Production-Ready
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The pseudocode above demonstrates the scoring logic, but a production deployment needs substantially more:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Dead letter queue and retry.** The DLQ pattern described in "Why These Services" is critical. Every failed scoring event must be captured, retried, and escalated if unresolved within 24 hours. Patients who fall through the cracks are exactly the ones who tend to need intervention most (complex patients with messy data).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Feature freshness guarantees.** The nightly Glue job means historical features could be up to 24 hours stale. For a patient admitted and discharged on the same day they had a prior admission, the feature store won't reflect today's admission in the historical count. Accept this as a known limitation or add a real-time update path for the feature store triggered by ADT events.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-site consistency.** If your health system has multiple hospitals, a patient discharged from Hospital A might have relevant history at Hospital B. The feature store needs to aggregate across all sites, which requires a unified patient identifier (MPI) or probabilistic matching.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Fairness validation.** Before going live, validate that model performance (AUC and calibration) is acceptable across racial, ethnic, age, and insurance subgroups. A model well-calibrated overall but poorly calibrated for Black patients or Medicaid patients is not acceptable for clinical use.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Clinical governance sign-off.** The CMO or a designated clinical committee must approve the model for use, the intervention protocols, and the escalation pathways. Document the validation study, known limitations, and the plan for ongoing monitoring.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
