[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 140     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m ### Performance Benchmarks
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 141     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 142     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | Metric | Expected Value | Notes |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 143     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m |--------|---------------|-------|
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 144     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | AUC-ROC (C-statistic) | 0.68-0.75 | Depends on feature richness; social determinants push toward upper range |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 145     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | Calibration slope | 0.90-1.10 | After Platt scaling; check quarterly |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 146     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | Brier score | 0.12-0.16 | Lower is better; baseline (prevalence) ~0.13 |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 147     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | Sensitivity at top 15% | 0.35-0.45 | Captures 35-45% of actual readmissions in top risk tier |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 148     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | PPV at top 15% | 0.28-0.38 | 28-38% of flagged patients actually readmit |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 149     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | Scoring latency | <500ms | End-to-end from feature assembly to score storage |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 150     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | Time from discharge to score | <2 hours | Includes ADT event propagation delay |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 151     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | Model retraining frequency | Monthly | Or when AUC drops below 0.65 |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 152     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 153     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m ### Where It Struggles
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 154     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 155     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **Patients with no prior history at your facility.** New patients or transfers from other systems have sparse feature vectors. The model defaults to population-level risk, which is less useful.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 156     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **Social determinant-driven readmissions.** A patient readmitted because they couldn't afford their medications or had no transportation to follow-up won't be well-predicted by clinical features alone.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 157     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **Planned readmissions misclassified as unplanned.** The CMS planned readmission algorithm isn't perfect. Some planned returns get labeled as failures, inflating your apparent readmission rate.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 158     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **Weekend and holiday discharges.** Patients discharged when follow-up resources are unavailable have elevated risk that's driven by system factors, not patient factors. The model may not capture this well unless day-of-week features are included.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 159     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **Rapidly changing care patterns.** If your hospital launches a new heart failure program that dramatically reduces CHF readmissions, the model trained on pre-program data will over-predict risk for CHF patients until retrained.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 160     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m 
